Shadowmere is a ruined frontier march-town northwest of Midgaard, built at a crossroads of military roads, farmland, and burial tracts. Originally a Crown-funded outpost for guarding transit, taxing goods, and processing war/plague dead before they reached core districts.

The Plague Mandate granted emergency powers: forced quarantine, immediate cremation, suspension of lineage appeals. No sunset clause was included. Temporary authority became permanent. The town became a mass-intake facility for dead and dying.

After the plague receded, four power blocs deadlocked over rollback. The Last Bell Crisis: three contradictory decrees (amnesty, lockdown, requisition) issued in one night. Governance collapsed into competing hostile systems.

Blight Hydrology: original drainage routed runoff through burial and quarantine zones. Alchemical waste and preservative salts entered the same channels. Sealed crypts flooded from below. Low fields became permanent toxic wetlands. The contamination is structural, not accidental.

Five factions claim legal authority; none hold legitimacy. The Oathbound March: undead soldiers executing obsolete military orders. The Crimson Household: aristocratic vampiric predators claiming bloodline continuity under the original charter. The Binder Collegium: necromancer-clerks who treat souls as ledger entries. The Gallows Syndicate: execution specialists who turned sentencing infrastructure into a commerce network. The Fen-Adapted Remnants: feral survivors who have adapted to the toxic marshland beyond any governance.

Shadowmere demonstrates institutional failure through unchecked emergency powers. Every faction still stamps, witnesses, and seals orders -- all legally grounded, all functionally predatory.

